Company Overview of General Motors Financial Company, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
General Motors Financial Company, Inc. provides automobile financing solutions in North America and internationally. It offers prime and sub-prime lending, and full credit spectrum leasing through franchised and independent dealers under the GM Financial and AmeriCredit brands for the customers who have limited access to automobile financing through banks and credit unions. The company also provides commercial lending products, such as wholesale or floorplan financing to new and used vehicle inventory; and dealer loans to finance parts and accessories, as well as improvements to dealership facilities, to provide working capital, and to purchase and finance dealership real estate. In addition...
General Motors Financial Company, Inc. provides automobile financing solutions in North America and internationally. It offers prime and sub-prime lending, and full credit spectrum leasing through franchised and independent dealers under the GM Financial and AmeriCredit brands for the customers who have limited access to automobile financing through banks and credit unions. The company also provides commercial lending products, such as wholesale or floorplan financing to new and used vehicle inventory; and dealer loans to finance parts and accessories, as well as improvements to dealership facilities, to provide working capital, and to purchase and finance dealership real estate. In addition, it offers finance and/or car-related insurance products, such as payment protection, gap, extended warranty, and motor insurance through third parties; and financing for fleets and storage centers, as well as customer services. The company was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas. General Motors Financial Company, Inc. is a subsidiary of General Motors Company.
