General Motors Financial Company, Inc. Key Developments

General Motors Financial Company, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Reports Net Charge-Offs for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for 2017
Jul 25 17
General Motors Financial Company, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $2,990 million compared to $2,138 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $356 million compared to $213 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $270 million compared to $143 million a year ago. Net income was $62 million compared to $189 million a year ago.

For the six months, the company reported total revenue of $5,738 million compared to $4,069 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $585 million compared to $406 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $449 million compared to $281 million a year ago. Net income was $264 million compared to $353 million a year ago.

For the second quarter ended June 30, 2017, the company reported net charge-offs was $130 million compared to $128 million a year ago.

The company expects its full year 2017 earnings to exceed full year 2016 earnings from continuing operations, which were $763 million. However, the company anticipates that its second half earnings will be down from the first half due to lower year-over-year and seasonally weaker used car pricing, higher lease returns and the retiming of some of its infrastructure spending and OpEx spending from the first half into the second half of the year.


General Motors Financial Company, Inc. expected to report Q2 2017 results on July 28, 2017. This event was calculated by Capital IQ (Created on July 25, 2017).
